         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">He is happy about the news in [ha-Kohen's] last letter.
                            thanks for a present sent to him. Z. gave his letter to Isaac Sforno and
                            admonished him personally for not taking action, Sforno then replied
                            that he was cognizant of his failure to act as required, but that he was
                            forced to provide food for his family. Sforno gained some relieve by the
                            coming of a non-Jew and was now in the position to appraise the work or
                            to return [ha-Kohen] his money. However, the commentary of R. Ḥayyim Del
                            Vecchio was not available for copying, as the copy of R. Provinzal could
                            not be found. Another (?) copy could be possibly made for a fee. </note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">זאת נחמתי בעניי כי
                        אמרתך</note>
         </notesStmt>
